          "None Specificed",
          "[Resource Usages per week]",
          "Authors exclusively use the fine-grained data from the LMS of interactions with the folders on both Weekdays and Sunday.",
          "GMM",
          "BIC",
          "3",
          "Cluster 1 (n=6): Lower total views in general and, correspondingly, lower final result.\n\nCluster 2 (n=69): More views on Weekdays than on Sunday.\n\nCluster 3 (n=61):\nMore views on on Sunday than Weekdays, even though not by a substantial margin. \n\nPerformance is indistinguishable for both of these clusters. ",
          "Cluster show that more activity tends to lead to better performance. However, whether the levels of activity come more during weekdays or weekends does not seem to have a significant impact.",
          "Clustering via GMM is introduced as a new approach to feature generation rather than what is usually used. ",
          "ingle course Data\n\nMay not generalize well to outside STEM\n"
        ]
      ],
