          "144 undergraduate students",
          "1 Practical Statistics Course",
          "LMS Logs, Institutuional Data, Learner Results",
          "[Demographics, Resource Usages per week]",
          "Every Week",
          "Authors collect information from the Student Registration System and  of the Student Interactions.\n\nEach week has a specific folder that contains the materials meant for the week → thus there is, at max, a total of 15 stages.\n\nAuthhors also compare 4 feature configurations:\n\n  1. Background, Continuous Assessment and Logs, \n  2. Background and Continuous Assessment,\n  3. Background, Continuous Assessment and cumulative activity for each folder,\n  4. Cluster variables\n\n",
          "Random Forest, BART, XGBoost, Principal Components Regression, SVM, MLP, Adaptive Regression Splines, kNN",
          "10-Fold Cross-Validation",
          "{MAE: 6.5 -  Week 6 BART with Cumulative Variables and Cluster Variables}",
          "Authors attempt do early prediction not only using the usual traininig paradigm on multiple features sets, but also try new approaches → cumulative variables and cluster variables on a Statistics course.\n\nResults show that it is possible to obtain good predictions by week 6/15 using this approach,",
          "Single course Data\n\nMay not generalize well to outside STEM\n\n"
        ]
      ],
