    {
      "id": "dff9f833-5a4d-4f0a-ad54-5a96e8713949",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "This work compares 8 distinct predictive algorithms to predict student performance (grade) in a statistics course. Authors also identify weeks 5-6 (pretty much halfway point) as the optimal time to make a prediction. Best model (BART) achieves 6.5% of MAE. Also, authors publish their code in a github repository.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "dff9f833-5a4d-4f0a-ad54-5a96e8713949",
